Extracting String Characters
There are 2 safe methods for extracting string characters:

1.charAt(position)
2.charCodeAt(position)

1 The charAt() Method
  The charAt() method returns the character at a specified index (position) in a string:
Example : var str = "HELLO WORLD";
          str.charAt(0);            // returns H

2 The charCodeAt() Method
  The charCodeAt() method returns the unicode of the character at a specified index in a string:
Example : var str = "HELLO WORLD";
          str.charCodeAt(0);         // returns 72


Converting a String to an Array
A string can be converted to an array with the split() method:
Example: var txt = "a,b,c,d,e";   // String
         txt.split(",");          // Split on commas
         txt.split(" ");          // Split on spaces
         txt.split("|");          // Split on pipe

note : If the separator is omitted, the returned array will contain the whole string in index [0].

1 if the separator is "", the returned array will be an array of single characters:

Example : var txt = "Hello";       // String
          txt.split("");           // Split in characters


